<!-- Begin Homepage -->

<div id ="carousel-container" class="row">
  <div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
    
    <!-- Carousel Controllers -->
    <ol class="carousel-indicators">
      <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
      <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="1"></li>
      <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="2"></li>
    </ol>
    
    <!---Carousel Content-->
    <div class="carousel-inner" id="scroll-0">
      
      <!---First Slide-->
      <div class="item active">
        <img src="<%= image_path 'create.jpg' %>" class="carousel-img" alt="First slide">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="carousel-caption">
            <div class="header-wrapper">
            <h2 class="homepage-header"><span class="slide-header">Collect</span></h2> <br />
            <p class="carousel-slide-text">Collect data from classroom experiments, online resources, or probeware systems, and manually upload your data to iSENSE. Use iSENSE mobile applications to automatically gather and upload data to iSENSE.
            </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!---End First Slide Content-->
      
      <!---Second Slide-->
      <div class="item">
        <img src="<%= image_path 'Share.jpg' %>" class="carousel-img" alt="Second slide">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="carousel-caption">
            <div class="header-wrapper">
            <h2 class="homepage-header"><span class="slide-header">Share</span></h2> <br />
            <p class="carousel-slide-text">
              Share data on iSENSE to facilitate collaboration and conduct meaningful conversations. Upload data to iSENSE via the website or mobile applications and access it from anywhere.
            </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!---End Second Slide Content-->
    
      <!---Last Slide-->
      <div class="item">
        <img src="<%= image_path 'Visualize.png' %>" class="carousel-img" alt="Third slide">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="carousel-caption">
            <div class="header-wrapper">
            <h2 class="homepage-header"><span class="slide-header">Visualize</span> </h2> <br />
            <p class="carousel-slide-text">
              Analyze and visualize data on a map, timeline, scatter plot, bar graph, histogram, pie chart, table, and more. Configure visualizations to best suit displaying your data, and save them to revisit your work at a later time.
            </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!---End Last Slide-->
    </div>
    <!---End Carousel Content-->
    
    <!---Carousel Controls-->
    
    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="prev"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left"></span></a>
    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="next"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span></a>
    <!---End Carousel Controls-->
    
  </div>
  <!---End Carousel-->
</div>
<!---End Carousel Container-->

<hr class="featurette-divider carousel-divider">

<!---Begin Featurette-->
<div class="row secondary-content">
  <div class="col-md-12 secondary-main-content">
    <div class="featurette">
      
      <!---Begin iSENSE Project Description-->
      <div class=" col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 isense-desc" id="scroll-1">
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12 what-is-isense">
          <h2 class="homepage-header">What is iSENSE?</h2>
          <br class="line"/> 
          <div class="homepage-text">
            <p class="featurette-text">
              iSENSE is a data collection and visualization tool for teachers and students to engage and interact with data in meaningful new ways.
            </p>
            <p class="featurette-text"> iSENSE is an easy and convenient platform for users to: </p>
            <p class="featurette-text"><span class="text-success featured-list">Collect </span> experimental data. </p>
            <p class="featurette-text"><span class="text-info featured-list">Share </span> data with the world. </p>
            <p class="featurette-text"><span class="text-primary featured-list">Visualize </span>data with robust analysis tools.</p> 
            <br />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12 teachers-love-isense">
          <hr class="featurette-divider hidden-md hidden-sm visible-lg visible-xs" />
          <h2 class="homepage-header"> Teachers Love iSENSE</h2>
          <br class="line"/> 
          <div class="homepage-text">
            <p class="featurette-text">
              "Students are able to make connections between mathematics and real life using iSENSE. For example, students are able to observe the linear relationship between a length of a forearm and height of a person. Students can also discover that coffee cooling is modeled by an exponential function by trying to determine which type of coffee cup keeps coffee hot the longest."
              <br />- Elaine G., Math Teacher
            </p>
            <p class="featurette-text">
              “Using a iSENSE Data Walk Android application with a seventh grade students was one of the most engaging and authentic learning activities of the year. Students used technology to learn about the physical science standard for graphing and interpreting distance and time."
              <br />-Barbara K., Science Teacher 
            </p> 
            <p class="featurette-text">
              "After attending a professional development workshop on using tablets in a classroom, I brought a Ticker Tape motion lab into the 21st century. Using the iSENSE DataWalk application on Android tablets with GPS, over 300 Physics students created accurate plots of their motion on a football field and analyzed the results on iSENSE. I called this lesson the Human Ticker Tape lab and used it to reinforce prior activities on motion concepts."
              <br />
              -Steve C., Physics Teacher
            </p>
            <hr class="featurette-divider">
          </div> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <!---End Project Description-->
      
      <!---Featured image -->
      <div class=" col-lg-8 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <hr class="featurette-divider teachers-love-isense-seperator hidden-lg" id="scroll-4" />
        <img src="<%= image_path 'feature-histogram.png' %>" id="main-image-featurette" class="featurette-image hidden-xs" alt="Featured Histogram">
        <hr class="featurette-divider mid-display-sep hidden-xs hidden-lg">

      </div>
      <!---End Featured Image-->

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="featurette-divider teachers-love-isense-seperator hidden-md hidden-sm hidden-xs" />
<!---End Featurette-->
<!---Begin Two-column layout-->
<div class="row ternary-content">
  <div class="container marketing two-col" id="scroll-2">
    
